<db:abstract>
<db:para>Demonstrates a simple message system using D-Bus.</db:para>
</db:abstract>
<db:pubdate>2025-06-29</db:pubdate>
<db:date>2025-06-29</db:date>
<db:authorgroup>
<db:author>
<db:orgname class="corporation">The Qt Company Ltd.</db:orgname>
</db:author>
</db:authorgroup>
</db:info>
<db:para><db:emphasis>Ping Pong</db:emphasis> is a command-line example that demonstrates the basics of <db:link xlink:href="qtdbus-index.xml">Qt D-Bus</db:link>. A message is sent to another application and there is a confirmation of the message.</db:para>
<db:section xml:id="running-the-example">
<db:title>Running the Example</db:title>
<db:para>To run the example from <db:link xlink:href="">Qt Creator</db:link>, open the <db:emphasis role="bold">Welcome</db:emphasis> mode and select the example from <db:emphasis role="bold">Examples</db:emphasis>. For more information, visit <db:link xlink:href="">Building and Running an Example</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:para>Run the <db:code>pong</db:code> application and run the <db:code>ping</db:code> application with the message as the argument.</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp" role="bad">$ ./pong &amp;
$ ./ping Hello
Reply was: ping(&quot;Hello&quot;) got called
</db:programlisting>
</db:section>
